<div class="content-section">
  <h2>The protocol: how to sequence interventions</h2>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">01</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Get a metabolic baseline</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">Order fasting insulin, fasting glucose, and HbA1c. Calculate HOMA-IR (fasting glucose &#215; fasting insulin &#247; 405). Add triglycerides and HDL-C &#8212; a triglyceride-to-HDL ratio above 3.0 is a strong surrogate signal for insulin resistance. If you have recent bloodwork, check whether fasting insulin was included. It almost certainly wasn&#8217;t.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Week 0</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">02</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Start moving &#8212; consistently</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">Begin with daily post-meal walks (10 to 15 minutes). Add 3 to 4 Zone 2 aerobic sessions per week (30 to 45 minutes each). Add 2 resistance training sessions per week. This exercise stack is the single highest-leverage intervention and produces measurable improvement within 2 to 4 weeks. Don&#8217;t wait for dietary changes to be perfect before starting.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 1&#8211;4</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">03</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Clean up the diet</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">Eliminate added sugar and refined carbohydrates as the first priority. Replace with whole foods: legumes, vegetables, whole grains, fatty fish, nuts, olive oil. Increase fiber to 25 to 30 grams per day. Shift to a consistent eating window of 8 to 10 hours. These changes compound with exercise rather than substituting for it.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 2&#8211;6</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">04</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Audit sleep quality</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">Establish a consistent sleep and wake schedule. Aim for 7 to 9 hours. Eliminate alcohol within 3 hours of bedtime. Keep the room cool and dark. This removes the metabolic headwind that blunts the effects of dietary and exercise changes.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 1&#8211;4</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">05</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Consider targeted supplements</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">If HOMA-IR is above 2.5 despite 8 weeks of consistent lifestyle changes, add berberine (500mg three times daily with meals). Test RBC magnesium and Vitamin D &#8212; correct deficiencies in either. These supplement interventions operate through different mechanisms than exercise and diet and are additive.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Weeks 6&#8211;10</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="phase-card">
    <div class="phase-number">06</div>
    <div>
      <div class="phase-title">Retest at 3 months</div>
      <div class="phase-desc">Retest fasting insulin, fasting glucose, and HbA1c. Recalculate HOMA-IR. Meaningful improvement is typically detectable within 4 to 8 weeks; the full effect of lifestyle changes is visible by 3 months. If HOMA-IR remains above 2.5 despite sustained effort, discuss metformin or GLP-1 options with your physician.</div>
      <div class="phase-timeline">Month 3</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

